cleveland mayor george voinovich entered 
the 1990 governors race thursday promising ohio the same 
leadership that he said made cleveland a municipal success story 
over the past decade 
cleveland is off of the rocks and on a roll our neighborhoods 
are better our jobs are up and the jokes are down said 
voinovich an unsuccesful 1988 republican us senate candidate 
onetime lieutenant governor former state representative and 
cuyahoga county auditor 
voinovich 52 brushed aside questions about his defeat in the 
sentate race last year by democratic sen howard metzenbaum whom 
voinovich accused during the campaign of being soft on child 
pornography 
ohios democratic chairman james ruvolo revived past 
complaints of negative campaigning by voinovich against metzenbaum 
last fall and said he wishes the mayor the same success he had 
last year 
gov richard celeste a democrat is barred by the state 
constitution from seeking a third consecutive term 
