civil rights leaders are suing the state 
of connecticut contending its schools make it impossible for poor 
minority students to get the same education as their white 
suburban counterparts 
the desegregation lawsuit was filed thursday in hartford 
superior court on behalf of a black hartford fourthgrader and 16 
other children and teenagers arguing that racial imbalance in 
hartford area schools violates the state constitutions guarantee 
against racial discrimination 
the lawsuit contends that black and hispanic innercity children 
and white suburban children are all suffering under greater 
hartfords racially divided school systems 
black children going to black schools and white children going 
