<TEXT>
dishes rattled and houses shook but no damages or injuries were 
reported from an earthquake centered in missouri and felt in five 
other states authorities said 
the earthquake hit at 1148 am cdt thursday and measured 47 
on the richter scale of ground motion it was centered in new 
madrid mo 10 miles north of blytheville ark 
the temblor in tennessee arkansas missouri and kentucky 
was the strongest in the region since 1976 said pat jorgenson 
spokeswoman for the us geological surveys national earthquake 
information center in golden colo 
david stewart director of the center for earthquake studies at 
southeast missouri state university in cape girardeau mo said 
the quake also was felt in mississippi and illinois 
mary hester of mayfield ky about 20 miles north of the 
tennessee border was perched on her roof painting when the 
earthquake hit the quake lasted about 15 seconds 
there was a loud boom and about that time everything went to 
shaking i dont know which was shaking worse me or the 
house ms hester said 
pemiscot county sheriffs deputy rodney ivie in missouri said 
his office had received many calls but none reporting damage or 
injuries 
they were worried because they werent sure what it was 
ivie said they had a pretty good idea you know but they wanted 
to make sure 
the new madrid seismic zone was the center of a series of great 
earthquakes that rocked the area during the winter of 181112 
officials have warned repeatedly that a serious earthquake can 
be expected during the next several years in the new madrid seismic 
area which stretches roughly from southern illinois to arkansas 
thursdays was the strongest quake in the region since march 25 
1976 when one registered 49 said jorgenson 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude so a reading of 75 means an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 6 severe damage 
a 7 reading is a major earthquake capable of widespread heavy 
damage 8 is a great quake capable of tremendous damage 
the richter scale was unavailable in 18111812 but those quakes 
have been estimated at 82 to 83 on the scale the new madrid 
quakes affected much of the eastern united states felt as far away 
as boston and washington dc but the immediate area then was 
sparsely settled and there was relatively little local damage 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

