those policies he added include interest rates those of 
you who are wise consumers understand that when you go to buy a car 
or a house or anything that requires you as a consumer to pay over 
a long period of time one of the most critical aspects of whether 
or not its a good deal for you is the rate of interest you will 
have to pay on the purchase 
president bush has said that he does not want the federal 
reserve board an independent body to concentrate so hard on 
fighting inflation that it tips the economy into a recession 
the fed has strong influence over interest rates through its 
control of the money supply largely exercised through purchases 
and sales of government bonds through rates it charges for use of 
its funds and through other regulations 
fed credit policies are made public only with a time lag the 
policymaking open market committee decided in february not to 
increase rates further for the moment but two weeks after that 
meeting the fed raised by onehalf percentage point to 7 percent 
the rate it charges member banks for funds 
the most recent figures show the economy expanding at an annual 
rate of 3 percent during the first three months of the year and 
inflation as measured by consumer prices increasing at an annual 
rate of 61 percent during the first quarter the highest rate in 
two years 
sununu said the budget agreement with congress would bring a 
deficit reduction of 65 billion to 75 billion and economic 
growth if it continues at the current rate would add 85 billion a 
year to federal revenue next year and the year after without new 
taxes 
compare that to what alternatives that are being proposed one 
of the alternatives is a gasoline tax increase he said 
i think you all remember what happened when we had significant 
increases in gasoline prices in the late 70s our economy was 
stifled if you want to match what you can get out of growth 
with a gasoline tax that would inhibit growth you would have to be 
looking at an 85cent per gallon increase 
i cant imagine anyone advocating such a policy and getting 
