campeau corps board of directors friday announced a 
realignment that establishes campeau as a holding company for its 
real estate and retailing operations in the united states and 
canada 
the restructuring of the torontobased corporation came as the 
result of a process that has been in the works since campeau 
acquired federated department stores inc in a 67 billion hostile 
takeover last may 
robert campeau will continue as chairman and chief executive 
ronald w tysoe formerly executive vice president and president of 
campeau us will take over as president and chief operating 
officer of the newly restructured company 
tysoe replaces james t roddy whose resignation was disclosed 
thursday 
roddy 45 and a veteran of the retail business worked closely 
on the takeover of federated there was no word on roddys plans 
and an announcement friday from campeau said only that he was 
leaving to pursue other career interests 
