involved with financial nuts and bolts of the federated purchase 
also submitted her resignation 
retail industry analysts said the changes in the corporate 
parent should have little direct bearing on campeaus department 
store businesses 
federated operates abraham and straus bloomingdales burdines 
and other chain stores also under campeaus corporate umbrella is 
allied stores corp which campeau acquired in 1986 for 34 
billion allied and federated have headquarters in cincinnati 
